{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: vitalsigns_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates a FSH Observation instance conforming to the HL7 vital signs
    profile. Each invocation produces one vital sign observation, which may
    carry either:
      (a) a single scalar measurement (valueQuantity), or
      (b) a set of component measurements (e.g. systolic + diastolic for
          blood pressure, expressed as Observation.component[]).

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    InstanceOf: http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/vitalsigns
    Category  : vital-signs (named slice [VSCat], from
                http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/observation-category)
    Status    : always #final for synthetic data

  THREE-COLUMN HTML TABLE
    Column 1 — Vital sign code display    (always present)
    Column 2 — Observation date           (always present; formatted d-M-Y)
    Column 3 — Measurement value(s)       (scalar or composite; "-" if absent)

  MEASUREMENT VALUE LOGIC  (three-branch decision)
    The template selects the representation for HTML td 3 and the FSH value
    element through a cascading if/elseif/else:

      Branch A — Scalar (valueQuantity):
        Condition: `vital.value.scale == "numeric"` OR
                   `vital.valueQuantity.scale == "numeric"`,
                   AND the value field is non-empty.
        Dual-path: both `vital.value.*` and `vital.valueQuantity.*` are
                   consulted via the null-coalescing operator `??` so that
                   the caller can supply either path.
        FSH output: valueQuantity.value, .code, .system (UCUM), .unit
        HTML output: "{value} {unit}" via addHTML_td

      Branch B — Component (Observation.component[]):
        Condition: `vital.component` is non-empty.
        Loop over `vital.component`, emitting one component[+] (or a named
        slice when `cmp.slice` is set) per entry. Each component carries
        its own code and valueQuantity.
        HTML output: composite string built by a second loop over the same
                     components, joining values with " / " and appending the
                     last component's unit: e.g. "120 / 80 mmHg".

      Branch C — No value available:
        HTML output: "-"
        No FSH rule is emitted.

  NULL-COALESCING OPERATOR (??)
    The `??` operator returns the left operand when it is defined and non-null,
    otherwise falls back to the right operand. This allows the template to
    accept value data under either `vital.value.*` or `vital.valueQuantity.*`
    without explicit conditional branches for each field:

      {{ vital.value.value ?? vital.valueQuantity.value }}

  |first FILTER
    `vital.code` is an array of coding objects. `|first` extracts the first
    element so that a single `{% set c = ... %}` variable can be used for all
    subsequent code/system/display accesses, avoiding repeated array indexing.

  NAMED COMPONENT SLICES
    When a component carries a `cmp.slice` value, the template emits a named
    slice reference rather than the append operator [+]:

      Named:   * component[{{cmp.slice}}].code = ...
      Indexed: * component[+].code = ...

    Named slices are used when the IG defines specific slice discriminators
    for component positions (e.g. `component[SystolicBP]` in a BP profile).
    When `cmp.slice` is empty, [+] is used for generic sequential indexing.

  HEAD SECTION NOTE
    The %%HEAD%% section is intentionally empty. No `emitHEAD()` call is made
    there, even though `addHEAD_th()` calls populate the HEAD bag. The HEAD
    bag is instead flushed inside `text.div` only, giving the inline FHIR
    narrative a complete table with headers. External consumers reading only
    the %%HEAD%% section will receive no output for this template.

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌──────────────────────────────┬──────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                     │ Type     │ Description                          │
  ├──────────────────────────────┼──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ instanceid                   │ string   │ Unique resource id; appended to       │
  │                              │          │ "Instance-Observation-" for the FSH  │
  │                              │          │ instance name.                       │
  │ patient.instanceid           │ string   │ UUID of the Patient resource.        │
  │ patient.name                 │ string   │ Full display name for the subject    │
  │                              │          │ Reference display string.            │
  │ vital.code                   │ object[] │ Array of coding objects for the      │
  │                              │          │ observation code. Only the first     │
  │                              │          │ element is used (via `\|first`).     │
  │   [0].system                 │ string   │   CodeSystem URI (e.g. LOINC).       │
  │   [0].code                   │ string   │   Observation concept code.          │
  │   [0].display                │ string   │   Display text for the vital sign.   │
  │ vital.date                   │ string   │ ISO 8601 effective date/dateTime.    │
  │                              │          │ Formatted d-M-Y in HTML.             │
  │ vital.value  (or)            │ object?  │ Scalar value data (Branch A).        │
  │ vital.valueQuantity          │ object?  │ Alternative path for scalar value;   │
  │                              │          │ `??` coalesces both paths.           │
  │   .scale                     │ string   │   "numeric" triggers Branch A.       │
  │   .value                     │ number   │   Numeric measurement value.         │
  │   .code                      │ string   │   UCUM unit code.                    │
  │   .unit                      │ string   │   Human-readable unit string.        │
  │ vital.component              │ object[] │ Array of component objects (Branch B)│
  │   [n].code                   │ object[] │   Array of codings (first used).     │
  │   [n].slice                  │ string?  │   Optional named slice identifier.   │
  │   [n].value  (or)            │ object?  │   Component scalar value.            │
  │   [n].valueQuantity          │ object?  │   Alternative path; `??` coalesces.  │
  │     .value                   │ number   │     Numeric measurement value.       │
  │     .code                    │ string   │     UCUM unit code.                  │
  │     .unit                    │ string   │     Human-readable unit string.      │
  └──────────────────────────────┴──────────┴──────────────────────────────────────┘

  CODESYSTEMS REFERENCED
    http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/observation-category — vital-signs
    http://unitsofmeasure.org (UCUM) — for all valueQuantity.system rules
    Observation code system — caller-supplied via vital.code[0].system

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-09-02
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-Observation-" ~ instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/vitalsigns
Title: "Vital Signs"
Description: "Vital Signs"
Usage: #inline

* id = "{{ instanceid }}"

{#
  ── HEAD bag: three-column table header ────────────────────────────────────
  Flushed only inside text.div; %%HEAD%% section is empty for this template.
#}
{{ addHEAD_tr() }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Vital Sign") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Date") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Measurement") }}
{{ addHEAD_trend() -}}

{#
  ── Fixed status ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  All synthetic vital sign observations are final.
#}
* status = #final

{#
  ── Category: named slice [VSCat] ───────────────────────────────────────────
  The vital signs profile requires the vital-signs category to be expressed
  using the named slice [VSCat] rather than a generic [0] index. This matches
  the slice discriminator defined in the HL7 vitalsigns profile.
#}
* category[VSCat].coding[0] = http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/observation-category#vital-signs "Vital Signs"

{{ addHTML_tr() }}

{#
  ── Observation code (td 1) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
  `vital.code` is an array; |first extracts the first coding object. A local
  variable `c` is set to avoid repeating `vital.code|first` across the three
  sub-fields (system, code, display).
#}
{% set c = vital.code|first %}
* code = {{ c.system }}#{{ c.code }} "{{ c.display }}"
{{ addHTML_td(c.display) }}

{#
  ── Patient reference ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#}
* subject = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"

{#
  ── Effective date (td 2) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Formatted d-M-Y (e.g. "14-Mar-1978") in the HTML cell.
#}
* effectiveDateTime = "{{ vital.date }}"
{{ addHTML_td(vital.date|date('d-M-Y')) }}

{# performer could be added here when PractitionerRole instances are available:
   * performer = Reference(urn:uuid:{practitionerrole-uuid}) "{practitioner-name}" #}

{#
  ── Measurement value (td 3) — three branches ──────────────────────────────

  Branch A: scalar valueQuantity
    Triggered when scale == "numeric" on either vital.value or vital.valueQuantity
    AND the value field is non-empty. The ?? operator coalesces both paths.
    All four FHIR Quantity sub-elements are emitted. UCUM is always the system.
#}
{% if (vital.value.scale == "numeric" or vital.valueQuantity.scale == "numeric") and (vital.value.value is not empty or vital.valueQuantity.value is not empty) %}
* valueQuantity.value  = {{ vital.value.value ?? vital.valueQuantity.value }}
* valueQuantity.code   = #{{ vital.value.code ?? vital.valueQuantity.code }}
* valueQuantity.system = "http://unitsofmeasure.org"
* valueQuantity.unit   = "{{ vital.value.unit ?? vital.valueQuantity.unit }}"
{{ addHTML_td((vital.value.value ?? vital.valueQuantity.value) ~ " " ~ (vital.value.unit ?? vital.valueQuantity.unit)) }}

{#
  Branch B: component-based value (e.g. blood pressure)
    Each entry in vital.component produces one component FSH slice.
    When cmp.slice is set (named discriminator), it is used as the index;
    otherwise [+]/[=] sequential indexing is used.
    After all FSH rules are emitted, a second loop assembles the HTML
    display string "value1 / value2 unit" using Twig's set-in-loop pattern.
#}
{% elseif vital.component is not empty %}
{% for cmp in vital.component %}
{% set c = cmp.code|first %}
{# Named slice when available; generic append index otherwise #}
{% if cmp.slice is not empty %}
* component[{{cmp.slice}}].code = {{ c.system }}#{{ c.code }} "{{ c.display }}"
{% else %}
* component[+].code = {{ c.system }}#{{ c.code }} "{{ c.display }}"
{% endif %}
* component[=].valueQuantity.value  = {{ cmp.value.value ?? cmp.valueQuantity.value }}
* component[=].valueQuantity.code   = #{{ cmp.value.code ?? cmp.valueQuantity.code }}
* component[=].valueQuantity.system = "http://unitsofmeasure.org"
* component[=].valueQuantity.unit   = "{{ cmp.value.unit ?? cmp.valueQuantity.unit }}"
{% endfor %} {# end: cmp in vital.component — FSH rules #}

{#
  Build the composite HTML display string: "120 / 80 mmHg"
  Two accumulators are maintained across the loop:
    cvalue — concatenates numeric values separated by " / "
    cunit  — captures the last component's unit (shared across components)
  loop.last prevents a trailing " / " after the final value.
#}
{% set cvalue = "" %}
{% set cunit  = "" %}
{% for cmp in vital.component %}
{% set cvalue = cvalue ~ (cmp.value.value ?? cmp.valueQuantity.value) %}
{% if not loop.last %}
{% set cvalue = cvalue ~ " / " %}
{% endif %}
{% set cunit = cmp.value.unit %}
{% endfor %} {# end: cmp in vital.component — HTML string build #}
{{ addHTML_td(cvalue ~ " " ~ cunit) }}

{#
  Branch C: no value available
    No FSH rule is emitted. The HTML cell shows "-" as a placeholder.
#}
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_td("-") }}
{% endif %}

{{ addHTML_trend() -}}

{#
  ── FHIR narrative ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Both HEAD and HTML bags are flushed inside text.div so the inline narrative
  includes the column header row as well as the data row. The %%HEAD%% section
  below is intentionally empty — see HEAD Section Note in the file header.
#}
* text.status = #generated
* text.div    = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<table class="hl7__ips">{{ emitHEAD() | raw }}{{ emitHTML() | raw }}</table>
</div>
"""

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{# Intentionally empty: HEAD bag is flushed only inside text.div above. #}

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHTML() | raw }}
